# Midnight chain version pins
# Midnight uses its own Substrate-based node — NOT cardano-node
# This file is here for consistency but Midnight does NOT use Dockerfile.cardano/apexfusion
# Last updated: 2026-07-16
#
# 1.0.1 GA notes (midnightntwrk/midnight-node@node-1.0.1, released 2026-07-14):
#   - Binary-only patch on the 1.x line — runtime-1.0.0 unchanged; no governance action.
#   - Defaults unsafe_allow_symlinks to false when missing from config (#1601).
#   - Regenerates Preview genesis / chain-spec so the Locked pool is non-empty for the
#     Cardano→Midnight bridge (#1699). **Preview requires a network reset** (wipe chain
#     state and resync). Preprod and Mainnet: pull image + rolling restart only.
#   - Git tree hash 73c0dfc01e7dadcf9aa07dc2bdecf2da7547b8c3; public Preview tip reports
#     version 1.0.1-24d3feb3 with new genesis 0x3c096de2….
#   - Upgrade procedure (Preview): pull 1.0.1 → wipe /node/chain/{chains,ledger_storage}
#     (keep keystore) → restart → confirm genesis matches rpc.preview.midnight.network.
#
# Prior GA: node-1.0.0 (2026-05-20). Sister pre-release line node-2.0.0-rc.* is ledger-9 /
# fresh-chain-only and is NOT an upgrade target for preview/preprod/mainnet.

# Midnight node is a pre-built image from midnightntwrk
MIDNIGHT_NODE_IMAGE=midnightntwrk/midnight-node
MIDNIGHT_NODE_VERSION=1.0.1

# Midnight does NOT use:
# - cardano-node (uses Substrate)
# - Guild Operators scripts
# - Mithril
# - CNCLI
# Midnight deployment is handled via its own K3s manifests in chains/midnight/k3s/
